<subSubSection id="D093A68308B99D69B9D2D98E5EE7CF63" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="5FFC1EB919B911DB56DCCAD48A65DF18" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8115A641410634DC83369DB4FB044FF1" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="49C30CAAF7677E0558D994629B647895" authorityName="Kinzelbach" authorityYear="1971" class="Insecta" family="Xenidae" genus="Xenos" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xenos minor" order="Strepsiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis id="AC5FA356764A37B74187FA6918203B8F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Xenos minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is synonymized under 
<taxonomicName id="C5EFF808F209CFCDB877D772272B80B6" genus="X." lsidName="X. vesparum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="vesparum">
<emphasis id="ED1B04F59AADFF3A0F72CD6D8AFBBDDB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. vesparum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the results of a recent molecular phylogeny of 
<bibRefCitation id="4E87710BDE5A52C1A69F42163CB24F31" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/syen.12460" author="Benda, D" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="252 - 265" refId="B4" refString="Benda, D, Votypkova, K, Nakase, Y, Straka, J, 2021. Unexpected cryptic species diversity of parasites of the family Xenidae (Strepsiptera) with a constant diversification rate over time. Systematic Entomology 46: 252 - 265, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/syen.12460" title="Unexpected cryptic species diversity of parasites of the family Xenidae (Strepsiptera) with a constant diversification rate over time." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/syen.12460" volume="46" year="2021">Benda et al. (2021)</bibRefCitation>
. Specimens morphologically corresponding to 
<taxonomicName id="94AA91EAF3F086225B021CC3902DFFA6" authorityName="Kinzelbach" authorityYear="1971" class="Insecta" family="Xenidae" genus="Xenos" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xenos minor" order="Strepsiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis id="70575C9AA20578DD7CBC75C292B916C1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Xenos minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were nested within the lineage of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A3C401B6CA4B3191B12E94B714294" baseAuthorityName="Rossi" baseAuthorityYear="1793" class="Insecta" family="Xenidae" genus="Xenos" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xenos vesparum" order="Strepsiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vesparum">
<emphasis id="5FA4307FE74C2E1A96E569B354458FCE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Xenos vesparum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The former taxonomy was probably misled by the large phenotypic variability of 
<taxonomicName id="BA8CC3BA7EB40D23F7228CC4C7977FF3" baseAuthorityName="Rossi" baseAuthorityYear="1793" class="Insecta" family="Xenidae" genus="Xenos" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xenos vesparum" order="Strepsiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vesparum">
<emphasis id="2EEC5DD9AE2C299E2C7ECA79E8ADDA21" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Xenos vesparum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, corresponding to different host taxa (smaller specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="3980DC3DD850DFEDD01358522D9CE67E" genus="X." lsidName="X. vesparum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="vesparum">
<emphasis id="3FB3A99F16225E1EB783069455693D2F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. vesparum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are associated with smaller individuals of 
<taxonomicName id="C54D94A1A365753626AD33FD94ED1179" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Polistes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polistes" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="24F00F7C69ADA755DF83E34E8B82E6AF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Polistes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp.).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
